42#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
43# include <config.h>
44#endif /* HAVE_CONFIG_H */
45#include <am_defs.h>
46#include <fsi_data.h>
47#include <fsinfo.h>
48
49
50static int
51write_export_info(FILE *ef, qelem *q, int errors)
52{
53 fsi_mount *mp;
54
55 ITER(mp, fsi_mount, q) {
56 if (mp->m_mask & (1 << DM_EXPORTFS))
57 fprintf(ef, "%s\t%s\n", mp->m_volname, mp->m_exportfs);
58 if (mp->m_mount)
59 errors += write_export_info(ef, mp->m_mount, 0);
60 }
61
62 return errors;
63}
64
65
66static int
67write_dkexports(FILE *ef, qelem *q)
68{
69 int errors = 0;
70 disk_fs *dp;
71
72 ITER(dp, disk_fs, q) {
73 if (dp->d_mount)
74 errors += write_export_info(ef, dp->d_mount, 0);
75 }
76
77 return errors;
78}
79
80
81int
82write_exportfs(qelem *q)
83{
84 int errors = 0;
85
86 if (exportfs_pref) {
87 host *hp;
88
89 show_area_being_processed("write exportfs", 5);
90 ITER(hp, host, q) {
91 if (hp->h_disk_fs) {
92 FILE *ef = pref_open(exportfs_pref, hp->h_hostname, gen_hdr, hp->h_hostname);
93 if (ef) {
94 show_new(hp->h_hostname);
95 errors += write_dkexports(ef, hp->h_disk_fs);
96 errors += pref_close(ef);
97 } else {
98 errors++;
99 }
100 }
101 }
102 }
103
104 return errors;
105}
